      "message": "I implemented it as a immediately-invoked lambda:\n\n  static pthread_key_t get_pthread_key() {\n    static pthread_key_t sKey \u003d []{\n        pthread_key_t key;\n        int result \u003d pthread_key_create(\u0026key, /*destructor\u003d*/nullptr);\n        if (result !\u003d 0) {\n            SK_ABORT(\"pthread_key_create failure: %d\", result);\n        }\n        return key;\n    }();\n    return sKey;\n  }\n\nTBH I just... like this version less? Feels like I\u0027m doing something tricky.\nOK if I stick with the struct?",
