      "writtenOn": "2020-10-21T14:52:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since you feel strongly about it, done. I\u0027m not sure I agree with your broader opinion that the `struct` is inherently weirder--it\u0027s just an older idiom, one that predates lambdas, but there\u0027s nothing necessarily worse about it. Any non-trivial codebase that predates C++11 is likely to contain this idiom somewhere unless someone took the time to rewrite them all (and since the result is ~equivalent, why would they).",
      "parentUuid": "688aa1d5_084d02b7",
